A situation where poor digital communication caused a significant problem can be seen when a student sent an email to a professor without a clear subject line, proper greeting, or complete information. 
The email was written in an informal tone and lacked clarity regarding the purpose of the message. As a result, the professor misunderstood the request and did not respond promptly, leading to the student missing an important academic deadline.

This issue could have been avoided by following proper email etiquette. 
The student should have included a clear subject line, used a respectful and formal tone, and structured the message logically with all necessary details. Clear and professional communication helps prevent misunderstandings and ensures timely responses. 
This example highlights the importance of maintaining proper digital communication standards in academic environments.
